# ${OS_NAME} Workspace Hub

You're at the top of ${USERNAME}'s ${OS_NAME} workspace hub. **This is an index, not a working directory** — almost every real task should `cd` into one of the subworkspaces first so you load *that* area's `CLAUDE.md` (the ICM "Layer 0" for that scope).

## Layout

```
~/${WORKSPACE_HUB_NAME}/                hub (you are here)
${SUBWORKSPACES_BLOCK}
```

The subworkspaces are symlinks to real folders one level up in `$HOME` — paths like `${HOME_DIR}/<subworkspace>/...` still work everywhere; this hub just gives the agent a clean entry point that excludes user dotfiles by default.

## How to route a task

| User intent | `cd` to |
|---|---|
| System-level tweak to this ${OS_NAME} machine (i3, xrdp, fonts, themes, autostart, etc.) | `uap/` |
| Anything else | the relevant subworkspace from the layout above; if unclear, ask the user which subworkspace owns it |

Each subfolder has its own `CLAUDE.md` with deeper context. Read it on entry.

## Out-of-scope (do NOT browse without explicit user request)

These live in `$HOME` but are not part of this workspace and likely contain secrets or sensitive config:

- `~/.ssh/`, `~/.gnupg/` — keys
- `~/.claude.json`, `~/.claude/` — Claude Code auth, tokens, transcripts
- `~/.config/Microsoft/`, `~/.config/google-chrome/`, `~/snap/firefox/` — browser profiles with saved credentials
- `~/.aws/`, `~/.azure/`, `~/.kube/`, `~/.docker/config.json` — cloud / cluster auth
- `~/.local/share/keyrings/`, `~/.gnome2/keyrings/` — passwords
- `~/uap.local/` — this machine's identity, secrets, custom assets

If a task genuinely needs one of these, ask the user first.

## House style

- Plain markdown, tables for routing, short sentences.
- No emojis unless asked.
- No trailing "here's what I just did" summaries — say what's next, not what's past.
- When a system-level change is made on this machine, also mirror it into `~/uap/configs/` and update `~/uap.local/identity.yaml` and re-run `~/uap/setup/apply.sh` so the deployment stays reproducible.
